# BLV Synth Data Collector

**Platform**: Isaac Sim 5.1.0 / Kit 107.3.3
**Python**: 3.11 (Isaac Sim's bundled interpreter)
**Controller**: Logitech F710 (XInput) or any Xbox-compatible gamepad
**GPU**: NVIDIA RTX (Replicator requires RTX for ray-traced captures)

An Omniverse Kit / Isaac Sim extension for synthetic data collection in blind/low-vision (BLV) accessibility object detection research. It provides:

- **Gamepad-driven FPS camera control** — fly a first-person camera through any USD stage with a Logitech F710 / Xbox controller.
- **Trajectory recording & playback** — record per-frame camera poses to JSON, replay them deterministically.
- **Replicator-based multi-modal capture** — RGB, semantic segmentation, colorized segmentation, and tight 2-D bounding boxes via `omni.replicator.core`.
- **USD asset browser with auto-labeling** — cycle through a folder of USD assets; each is loaded as a reference and tagged with a semantic class.
- **Location management** — per-environment named spawn points. Saved transforms follow the asset across capture runs.
- **Collect All Data** — one-click matrix capture across every environment × location × trajectory × asset in your project.
- **Headless CLI** — run any of the above from the shell without opening Isaac Sim's window.

---

